subject: Avoid an AI adoption nightmare
body:
----------
Hot water can freeze faster than cold.

It’s called the Mpemba effect, and yes,  it makes zero intuitive sense.

Science: 1. Common sense: 0.

_Love or hate this intro? Hit reply and tell us why!_

**What’s in store:**

* AI didn’t fail your company; your training did. Here’s what LinkedIn's top voice, **Edward Frank Morris**, had to say about this. 

* The military just got a seat at the** AI table.**

* **Around the web: **The Switch 2 is even harder to repair than the original.



_Read Time: 6 minutes_


--------------------
###### **CREATOR COLUMN**

## Your AI Strategy Looks Great on Paper. So Did the Titanic.

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/d68074ac-e637-4361-9683-53e36587d6da/u8676618187_a_pixel_art_style_of_a_A_futuristic_city_skyline__0cd81f96-b8bd-42bb-95db-e5a915850afe_3.png?t=1749310251)
Follow image link: (https://www.mindstream.news/)
Caption: 

It started with excitement.

A senior VP whispered “Copilot” like it was a cheat code for life. Someone built a slide deck with floating brains and said the word “disruption” so many times you thought the office Wi-Fi was breaking.

You launched the AI rollout. There was a logo. A tagline. Maybe even a Slack emoji.

And then. Silence.

Except for that one guy in Marketing who asked Copilot to draft a campaign brief and ended up with an apology letter to a houseplant. Finance tried using ChatGPT to summarise Q3, and it hallucinated a merger with Blockbuster.

Now leadership is asking questions. Annoyed ones. Like “Why are we spending $300K on something nobody’s using?” and “Why does the AI think our company is based in Atlantis?”

You had a dream. What you got was a polite breakdown in autocomplete form.

### **Here’s what’s really happening inside your AI adoption nightmare:**

* **Your people are pretending to get it.**

They nod in meetings but secretly Google “what is a prompt” during lunch. Everyone’s afraid to look dumb, so no one asks anything. Except that one intern who uses AI fluently and terrifies everyone.

* **Training was a TED Talk, not a toolbox.**

You gave them a vision of the future but forgot to hand out the map. Or snacks. So now they’re just confused and mildly hungry.

* **The fear is real.**

A third of your staff thinks AI is quietly preparing their redundancy letters. The rest think it's a passing fad, like QR codes in restaurants.

* **ROI is missing, presumed dead.**

You bought licenses but didn’t build behaviour. Now the dashboards show “low engagement,” and your CFO is staring at you like you just Venmo’d OpenAI your vacation fund.

* **Governance? You mean vibes.**

Compliance wants a policy. Legal wants reassurance. The AI just wrote a sonnet about GDPR. No one is sleeping well.

### **Let’s fix this. Here’s what actually works:**

**1. Start with your AI Champions**

Find the 5 to 10% of your team who are naturally curious and mildly dangerous with tech. Give them early access. Let them break things.

* Encourage experimentation.

* Capture their wins, even the small ones.

* Let them spread the gospel internally like it’s a secret club and they’ve got the password.

**2. Train like you actually want people to use it**

No vague “future of work” webinars. Give real, short, role-specific training.

* 15 to 20-minute modules with real examples.

* Show marketers how to generate copy, analysts how to summarise chaos.

* Practice prompts, not just theory.

If they can’t use it after 10 minutes, they never will.

**3. Incentivise usage like it’s a game**

People do amazing things when they know someone’s watching and there’s a chance of snacks or clout.

* Reward creative use cases.

* Celebrate wins in team meetings or newsletters.

* Turn “most improved prompt” into an actual thing.

If you make it fun, they’ll come back.

**4. Talk about job security, loudly and often**

Reassure your teams that AI isn’t here to replace them. It’s here to delete their worst tasks.

* Host open Q&A sessions.

* Share examples of time saved, stress reduced, and creativity boosted.

* Make AI feel like a co-pilot, not a grim reaper in a hoodie.

**5. Track adoption and support it like a product launch**

Treat AI like a living tool, not a one-off rollout.

* Use analytics to see what’s actually getting used.

* Set up a help desk or Slack channel where people can ask questions like “Why does ChatGPT keep saying 'dear sir'?”

* Adjust your training and nudges based on real feedback.

AI won’t fix your company.

But your people might. If you give them the right tools, the right story, and just enough chaos to make it interesting.

Because in the end, adoption isn’t about the tech.

 It’s about getting Karen from HR to stop fear-scrolling AI news and start using Copilot to draft her memos in half the time.

That’s the real transformation.

And no slide deck will ever beat that.

_Today’s column was written by __[Edward Frank Morris](https://www.linkedin.com/in/edwardfmorris/)__!_


--------------------
##### **On This Day**


--------------------
**June 9th 1534 – **French explorer Jacques Cartier[ became ](https://www.ebsco.com/research-starters/history/europeans-discover-st-lawrence-river)the first European to describe and map the Saint Lawrence River, paving the way for French colonisation in North America.


--------------------
##### **Trending Tools **


--------------------
[Boardmix AI](https://boardmix.com/): A whiteboard that actually thinks. Generate flowcharts, diagrams, mind maps, and strategy boards just by typing what you need.

[CastPush](https://il.ly/blog/castpush): One post, everywhere. CastPush lets you publish to multiple platforms, email, Twitter, blogs, and more, in one click. AI rewrites the message to fit each channel.

[GigaBrain](https://thegigabrain.com/): Turn Reddit into a research tool. GigaBrain scans subreddits and comments to find credible answers, summarise insights, and show real user-backed opinions.

[Phind](https://www.phind.com/): Dev questions? Solved. Phind is a search engine built for developers that gives instant, AI-generated coding answers with links and context.

[Userdesk](https://userdesk.io/): Your customer support desk, powered by AI. Build a smart chatbot trained on your own docs to answer questions instantly on your website.


--------------------
###### **ANTHROPIC **

## [Anthropic just hired a defence insider](https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/06/anthropic-appoints-a-national-security-expert-to-its-governing-trust/)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c2b130f8-ecd0-450e-8dcc-e32353f39cce/u8676618187_a_pixel_art_style_of_a_humanoid_robot_in_a_suit_h_cc6bdacc-8370-427c-9b0c-e6a7f45d437d_2.png?t=1749310991)
Follow image link: (https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/06/anthropic-appoints-a-national-security-expert-to-its-governing-trust/)
Caption: 

Anthropic has brought in Richard Fontaine, a well-known national security expert, to join its long-term benefit trust, a group that [helps shape](https://www.anthropic.com/news/national-security-expert-richard-fontaine-appointed-to-anthropic-s-long-term-benefit-trust) the company’s direction and keeps safety front and centre. 

Fontaine’s background includes advising the late Senator John McCain, teaching security studies at Georgetown, and leading a major U.S. think tank. 

His arrival comes just after Anthropic introduced new AI models aimed at national security work.

The trust has the authority to elect board members and already includes leaders from the fields of public health and global development. 

**Here’s what’s going on:**

* Fontaine joins the trust to help steer AI in sensitive national security contexts.

* Anthropic is expanding its work with defence agencies through major partnerships.

* Other big AI labs are also moving into military and classified projects.

### **This hire has clearance**

Fontaine won’t have a financial stake in the company but will play a key role in guiding decisions where AI meets security.

Anthropic is leaning further into defence work. 

Last year, it [teamed up ](https://www.forwardfuture.ai/p/anthropic-teams-with-palantir-and-aws-for-defense-ai)with Palantir and AWS to offer its AI tools to military customers. 

And it’s not the only one, OpenAI, Meta, Google, and Cohere are all taking steps to make their AI more defence-ready.

Fontaine joining the trust feels like when your dad shows up at your group project.


--------------------
##### **Mindstream Picks**


--------------------
**Recommended Reading: **Tech moves fast. If you’re still catching up on last quarter’s trends, you’re already behind. CIO Upside is the free newsletter helping CIOs stay ahead with smart takes on AI, cloud, cybersecurity, and more. [Subscribe for free](https://www.thedailyupside.com/welcome-to-cio-upside/?utm_source=Mindstream&utm_medium=Newsletter&utm_campaign=Mindstream_02_01_2025) and stay ahead.

**Space**: ispace’s second moon mission, Resilience, likely [crashed](https://spacenews.com/second-ispace-lunar-lander-presumed-lost/) during its June 5 landing attempt. The lander was targeting Mare Frigoris and was expected to run for about two weeks on solar power before lunar nightfall.

**Crypto**: Lagrange’s token has plummeted[ 37% ](https://crypto.news/lagrange-rockets-then-reenters-reality-as-hype-fizzles-post-listing/)from its weekly peak, now sitting at $1.13 with a $220 million market cap. 

**Games**: Marvel has[ announced](https://metro.co.uk/2025/06/07/neil-patrick-harris-deadpool-new-marvel-vr-game-23349773/) a new Deadpool VR game at Summer Game Fest, with Neil Patrick Harris set to voice Deadpool.

**Don’t Miss:** iFixit gave the new Switch 2 a 3/10 repairability score, calling it even [harder to fix](https://www.theverge.com/news/681568/ifixit-nintendo-switch-2-repairability) than the original, with glued-in batteries, soldered parts, hidden screws, and no official repair support, making common fixes like joystick drift a serious challenge.

**What’s in store:**

* What happens when** you block chips **but forget the chips you already sold?

* This is what happens when your **terms of service **aren’t clear.

* **Around the web: **Xbox is now letting Game Pass Ultimate users stream their own console games on PC.

* How AI [**changed social media**](https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/ai-social-media-strategy?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-17&utm_content=native-ads) for good.

_Read Time: 5 minutes_


--------------------
###### **NVIDIA**

## [Nvidia’s chips are banned, so how are China’s models still thriving?](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/07/16/jensen-huang-china-ai-models-nvidia-gears-up-to-resume-chip-exports-.html)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/3b5af864-a854-4404-87c6-16a5112f0c4c/u8676618187_Pixel_art_style_of_a_robed_figure_handing_a_glowi_72a6cae6-f50d-45d3-ba6f-0bfa9c9c2034_3.png?t=1752671814)
Follow image link: (https://www.cnbc.com/2025/07/16/jensen-huang-china-ai-models-nvidia-gears-up-to-resume-chip-exports-.html)
Caption: 

Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang [has praised](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/07/16/jensen-huang-china-ai-models-nvidia-gears-up-to-resume-chip-exports-.html) China’s top generative AI models, DeepSeek, Alibaba, Tencent, MiniMax, and Baidu’s Ernie, describing them as “world-class” and crediting their open-source approach for pushing AI development forward globally. 

His comments came just as Nvidia announced plans to restart shipments of its H20 chips to China, following a pause earlier this year due to U.S. export rules.

Despite ongoing restrictions, more than 1.5 million developers in China are actively building on Nvidia’s platforms. 

Huang highlighted open-source models like Moonshot’s [Kimi K2](https://opendatascience.com/alibaba-backed-moonshot-unveils-kimi-k2-open-source-ai-model-outperforms-chatgpt-and-claude-in-coding/#:~:text=In%20benchmark%20comparisons%2C%20Moonshot%20states,among%20developers%20and%20early%20adopters.), which recently claimed better coding performance than ChatGPT and Claude. 

He also pointed out how AI is already baked into everyday Chinese apps like WeChat, Taobao, and Douyin.

**Quick takes:**

* Nvidia’s H20 chips are set to return to China after U.S. approval.

* China’s open-source AI models are accelerating fast and making waves globally.

* Tensions are still there, but both sides are loosening their grip slightly.

Nvidia has taken a financial hit from the restrictions, missing out on billions in sales. 

But after recent[ trade talks ](https://www.theguardian.com/business/2025/jun/27/us-china-rare-earth-shipments-deal)between the U.S. and China, there are signs of a slight shift, with the U.S. softening some export rules and China resuming rare earth shipments.

Nvidia is in its soft launch era with China again.

###### **AI SOCIAL MEDIA**

## [Fresh Insights From 1,100+ Social Media Experts](https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/ai-social-media-strategy?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-17&utm_content=native-ads)

Caption: 

It's just not fair. Social media marketers used to have the privilege of toiling over content, customer research, and personalisation from scratch. But now AI has simplified the struggle.

You’ll learn:

* Why AI makes an excellent teammate

* 7 tools worth adding to your tech stack

* 6 ways to innovate inside your company

We don't write the rules. We just want to help you win.

Stay Sharp, Marketers → (https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/ai-social-media-strategy?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-17&utm_content=native-ads)


--------------------
##### **On This Day**


--------------------
**On this day in 1975**, a U.S. Apollo spacecraft [docked](https://starwalk.space/en/news/apollo-soyuz-mission-end-of-the-space-race) with a Soviet Soyuz capsule in orbit – the first joint mission between the two superpowers. 


--------------------
##### **AI or Real? **


--------------------
View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/b173b519-f181-4af6-ad95-12ab5c7d7e40/Tokyo.png?t=1752667447)
Caption: 

Tokyo is a dream. Is this picture of it real?

Vote below!

The poll results and correct answer will be revealed in tomorrow’s Mindstream!


--------------------
###### **AI TECH **

## [The clause that broke the internet, for a second](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cp8mp79gyz1o)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/edb85e58-d0b2-438c-ae72-eb98863ce7d3/u8676618187_Pixel_art_style_of_a_person_looking_confused_sitt_76d4eaa4-c41a-4cbc-bf35-11b3e78dec1f_2.png?t=1752703006)
Follow image link: (https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cp8mp79gyz1o)
Caption: 

WeTransfer has confirmed it doesn’t use [any files](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cp8mp79gyz1o) shared on its platform to train AI. 

The company came under fire after updating its terms of service, which many users took to mean their content could be used for AI purposes.

WeTransfer says the clause was only meant to cover moderation tools that might use AI to flag harmful content, not to train models or sell user data. 

After the backlash, it updated the wording to make things clearer. 

The [new terms](https://wetransfer.com/explore/legal/terms), kicking in on 8 August, say users give permission to use content for running and improving the service, in line with the privacy policy.

Several creatives said they were thinking of switching platforms, worried about how their work might be used. 

**Three things to know:**

* WeTransfer says it does not train AI models on your files or sell your data.

* It updated the wording in its terms to clear up any confusion.

* Legal experts warn vague policies can put users in a tight spot.

### **Same clause, new spin**

A similar situation happened with [Dropbox i](https://www.computing.co.uk/news/4157118/dropbox-backlash-openai-sharing)n late 2023, when users voiced concerns about AI, prompting the company to issue a clarification.

Legal experts say these kinds of terms can be risky, especially as tech firms push to use more data for AI. 

For users, sudden changes like this can feel like they’re being left with little say.

Dropbox walked so WeTransfer could…walk back.

--------------------

[Nonlinear](https://careerhannah.substack.com/?utm_source=mindstream&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=mindstream&utm_id=mindstream) [Techies](https://careerhannah.substack.com/?utm_source=mindstream&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=mindstream&utm_id=mindstream) is a weekly email of hand-picked generalist roles for sharp operators who want to make an impact.

**Space**: Astronomers find [distant object ](https://www.space.com/astronomy/solar-system/astronomers-discover-a-cosmic-fossil-at-the-edge-of-the-solar-system-is-this-bad-news-for-planet-9)beyond Pluto, hinting Planet Nine may be even farther out, or no longer in our solar system.

**Crypto**: Windtree Therapeutics to buy $60m in BNB, with [plans](https://crypto.news/nasdaq-listed-windtree-to-buy-60m-bnb-in-crypto-strategy-push/) to expand its crypto treasury strategy to $200m.

**Games**: Ubisoft [names ](https://variety.com/2025/gaming/news/ubisoft-spinoff-ceos-christophe-derennes-charlie-guillemot-1236453661/)Christophe Derennes and Charlie Guillemot co-CEOs of new spinoff focused on growing Assassin’s Creed, Rainbow Six, and Far Cry.

**Don’t Miss:** Xbox is[ now testing](https://www.theverge.com/news/707739/xbox-stream-your-own-game-pc-app) a feature that lets Game Pass Ultimate users stream their owned console games on PC, helping save storage space on large titles. Over 250 games are supported, with more console-only and Play Anywhere games expected to join the list soon.

subject: Re: Nobel para Francesca Albanese
body:
Queridos amigos y amigas:

Más de450 000 personas de todo el mundo están a favor de que Francesca Albanese y los médicos de Gaza reciban el Nobel de la Paz por su labor. Mientras el gobierno de Trump sanciona a la experta en derechos humanos de la ONU, debemos demostrar que el mundo apoya a quienes no se acobardan ante los poderosos y alzan la voz sin miedo. ¿Te sumas?
Firma ya ( https://secure.avaaz.org/campaign/es/stand_with_francesca_loc/?bLPNEjb&v=168195&cl=22229751265&_checksum=0bc8a141216a9e8dd4734951829e29c2fee6e68814b5569dbd20fdd61671e5dd&utm_source=email&utm_medium=blast_email&utm_campaign=168195 ) 

----------

EE UU acaba de anunciar sanciones contra Francesca Albanese, experta de la ONU en derechos humanos, por denunciar la situación de Gaza. La mejor manera de demostrar qué opina la ciudadanía de esta intimidación es movilizarnos en masa para que le concedan junto a los médicos de Gaza el Nobel de la Paz, el mismo galardón que, según Netanyahu, merecería ganar Trump… Las nominaciones para Albanese están ganando fuerza, súmate ya: 

FIRMA YA ( https://secure.avaaz.org/campaign/es/stand_with_francesca_loc/?bLPNEjb&v=168195&cl=22229751265&_checksum=0bc8a141216a9e8dd4734951829e29c2fee6e68814b5569dbd20fdd61671e5dd&utm_source=email&utm_medium=blast_email&utm_campaign=168195 ) 

Queridos amigos y amigas:

Siempre se ha atrevido a hablar sin miedo. Ahora, el gobierno de Trump castiga a Francesca Albanese, la Relatora Especial de la ONU por los Territorios Palestinos, anunciando sanciones contra ella.
Pero las nominaciones para que Francesca Albanese se alce con el mayor reconocimiento por la paz también están ganando fuerza. Entretanto, Albanese se enfoca en quienes corren más peligro: todas las personas que sufren en Gaza.

¡Somos millones de personas repartidas en el mundo entero! Podemos utilizar este momento parademostrar nuestro respaldo a Francesca y decir alto y claro que ella y los médicos de Gaza se merecen el premio más prestigioso del mundo. Súmate a la petición ahora y difunde por todos lados: 

Firma ya: Nobel de la Paz para Francesca Albanese ( https://secure.avaaz.org/campaign/es/stand_with_francesca_loc/?bLPNEjb&v=168195&cl=22229751265&_checksum=0bc8a141216a9e8dd4734951829e29c2fee6e68814b5569dbd20fdd61671e5dd&utm_source=email&utm_medium=blast_email&utm_campaign=168195 ) 

Francesca Albanese ha sido una de las voces más críticas con la situación en Gaza. Ha denunciado las violaciones de derechos humanos y

no se ha acobardado a la hora de señalar a los políticos y empresas que se lucran con el genocidio, aun a riesgo de situarse en la mira de Israel y EE UU. Y tanto los médicos residentes en Gaza como los que han llegado de fuera para ayudar han servido como autoridad moral dando la voz de alarma una y otra vez para incitar a los dirigentes políticos a actuar.

Albanese siempre ha usado la autoridad que su papel de experta independiente le confiere para defender a quienes lo necesitan y ahora se merece que hagamos lo mismo por ella.L a mejor manera de responder a las amenazas y la intimidación es demostrarle a ella y a los médicos de Gaza que cientos de miles de personas de todo el mundo los apoyan y consideran que merecen el Nobel de la Paz.

Súmate para darle fuerza a la petición que haremos llegar al despacho de Francesca Albanese, a los médicos y a los medios de comunicación.

Firma ya: Nobel de la Paz para Francesca Albanese ( https://secure.avaaz.org/campaign/es/stand_with_francesca_loc/?bLPNEjb&v=168195&cl=22229751265&_checksum=0bc8a141216a9e8dd4734951829e29c2fee6e68814b5569dbd20fdd61671e5dd&utm_source=email&utm_medium=blast_email&utm_campaign=168195 ) 

Cuando gente valiente como Francesca Albanese asume riesgos personales al ejercer su derecho a hablar sin miedo, tiene que saber que no está sola, que cientos de miles de personas en todo el mundo estamos con ella y consideramos que su importantísima labor es digna del reconocimiento internacional, no de sanciones. Suma tu nombre a nuestra carta y reenvíala entre amistades y familiares a quienes podría interesar. Avaaz se encargará de hacérsela llegar a la propia Albanese.

Con esperanza,
Antonia, Harriet, Huiting, Chris, Marco y el equipo de Avaaz

Más información: Francesca Albanese, relatora de la ONU para Palestina: EE.UU. quiere intimidarme con métodos mafiosos ( https://efe.com/mundo/2025-07-11/francesca-albanese-relatora-onu-palestina-reaaciones/ ) (EFE) Estados Unidos: Las sanciones contra la relatora especial de la ONU Francesca Albanese, una deplorable afrenta a la justicia internacional ( https://www.es.amnesty.org/en-que-estamos/noticias/noticia/articulo/estados-unidos-las-sanciones-contra-la-relatora-especial-de-la-onu-francesca-albanese-una-deplorable-afrenta-a-la-justicia-internacional/ ) (Amnistía Internacional) Francesca Albanese; nominada al Nobel de la Paz ( https://www.reflexionyliberacion.cl/ryl/2025/07/10/francesca-albanese-nominada-al-nobel-de-la-paz/ ) (Reflexión y Liberación) 

Avaaz es una red global de campañas de 70 millones de personas que trabaja para garantizar que las opiniones y valores de la gente en todo el planeta modelen los procesos de toma de decisiones a nivel mundial. "Avaaz" significa "voz" o "canción" en muchos idiomas. Los miembros de Avaaz son de todas las naciones del mundo; nuestro equipo está ubicado en 18 países a lo largo de 6 continentes y opera en 22 idiomas. Para saber más sobre las últimas campañas de Avaaz, haz clic aquí ( https://www.avaaz.org/es/highlights/ ) , o síguenos en Facebook ( https://www.facebook.com/Avaaz ) , X ( https://twitter.com/Avaaz ) o Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/avaaz_org/ ) . 

Te hiciste miembro del movimiento de Avaaz y comenzaste a recibir estos mensajes cuando firmaste la campaña "Europa y EE.UU -- es hora de salvar a los leones africanos" el 2015-07-31 usando el correo electrónico jcas3322@gmail.com.

Para asegurarte de que los correos de Avaaz lleguen a tu buzón, añade avaaz@avaaz.org a tu lista de contactos. Para cambiar tu correo electrónico, idioma de preferencia u otra información personal,contáctanos ( https://www.avaaz.org/es/contact/ ) o simplemente haz clic aquí para darte de baja ( https://secure.avaaz.org/page/es/unsubscribe/?v=168195&cid=54807&source=blast_footer ) . 

Para ponerte en contacto con Avaaz, no respondas a este correo. Mejor escríbenos a:

www.avaaz.org/es/contact ( https://www.avaaz.org/es/contact ) 

27 Union Square West

Suite 500
New York, NY 10003

https://www.facebook.com/Avaaz 

https://x.com/Avaaz 

https://www.instagram.com/avaaz_org/ 

https://www.tiktok.com/@avaaz.org

subject: Re: Información
body:
Buenos días, es un gusto atenderle. en el pdf adjunto puede verificar las
modalidades disponibles para Cursos Intensivos y Regulares de Campus Central



*Precio de cursos Intensivos:* Q380.00 Mensuales.
*Precio de cursos Regulares:* Q450.00 cada 2 Meses.



*¿Cuál es la diferencia de un curso Intensivo a un curso Regular?*
La diferencia es que en un curso Intensivo usted avanza un nivel al mes y
en un curso Regular usted avanza un nivel cada 2 meses.





*Para enviarle todo el proceso necesitamos que nos indique bajo qué
modalidad desea tomar su curso, un screenshot de su último curso aprobado
desde AppUmg en donde aparezca su nombre y su curso de inglés. *



*En caso no haya tomado curso enviarnos foto de su resultado de
Ubicación Vigente. El resultado de ubicación tiene 6 meses de vigencia. Por
favor enviarnos también su número de carnet de carrera completo. *



*En caso usted desee ingresar directamente a Principiante 1 por favor
indicarnos que desea tomar el curso Principiante 1 como asunto del correo,
Indicarnos la modalidad que desea tomar el curso y su número de carnet de
carrera completo.- *



Por su atención a lo expuesto reciba mis muestras de agradecimiento
Cordialmente Esc. de Idiomas

subject: Build computer vision applications fast
body:
Computer vision is at its best when you combine fine-tuned models with pre-set logic and flexible integrations. Roboflow makes this process easy and pain-free.

For example, you can layer multiple models in one piece of logic like "if an image contains a container, send it to ChatGPT to read the ID".

Try some of the most popular use cases, like sending receipt values to Slack ( https://blog.roboflow.com/how-to-read-receipts-with-ai/?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email ), transforming outfits with generative AI ( https://blog.roboflow.com/transforming-outfits-with-roboflow-workflows/?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email ), or counting objects on a conveyor belt ( https://blog.roboflow.com/counting-objects-conveyor-belt/?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email ).

Build with Workflows ( app.roboflow.com/workflows?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email )
Any workflow can easily be deployed on your cloud, with Roboflow, or on the edge. Workflows come with advanced video tooling like object tracking out-of-the-box.

Happy Building,
The Roboflow Team

 

 

Need help?
----------

Whether you need help with Roboflow, or computer vision in general, we have a variety of resources for you.

Roboflow Documentation ( https://docs.roboflow.com/?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email )

View an overview of Roboflow's functionalities with examples and code snippets.

Roboflow Forum ( https://discuss.roboflow.com/?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email )

Ask questions and get help from the Roboflow team and other users in the community.

Weekly Webinar ( http://roboflow.com/webinar?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email )

Join our team for a live product webinar and Q&A session every Tuesday.

Contact Sales ( https://roboflow.com/sales?utm_campaign=Feb+2025+Onboarding+Emails&utm_content=All+about+deployment&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=email )

Need more flexible plan options or curious about bulk discounts? Get in touch with our sales team.

subject: Vibe Coding: We tried it
body:
----------
“A Void” is a 280-page novel that never uses the letter E.

It’s a translation of Georges Perec’s lipogram, a full detective story with the most common letter in English completely missing.

Forget plot twists, this is alphabet warfare.

**Reminder**: our referral competition is live! The person who sends the most readers to Mindstream by July 19 using their referral link wins VIP tickets to INBOUND! Get your link from the recommendation section at the very bottom.

**What’s in store:**

* Ever crash out **while** **coding**? SAMSIES. We have a guide that I’ll help you ✨_keep it together_ ✨while coding, using none other than… Claude.

* **Poll of the week: **Do you fact-check AI?

* Learn how to write the [**best prompts**](https://offers.hubspot.com/tina-huang-ai-prompt-guide?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-06&utm_content=native-ads)!

_Read Time: 4 minutes_


--------------------
###### **CLAUDE FOR CODERS**

## Vibe Coding with Claude: a deep dive

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/31ff3ad5-abf6-4cd2-b1b6-df2d0f468c8c/0_0.jpeg?t=1751040721)
Follow image link: (https://www.mindstream.news/)
Caption: 

Coding is _hard_.

If you’ve ever tried and rage-quit halfway through a tutorial, you’re not alone. Learning how to code is a long and arduous process that’s not for the faint of heart.

And, for startup dreamers with big ideas and little patience to learn how to code (and, little budget to hire a developer to do it), this can be discouraging.

But, Claude can help your ideas come to life. 

I started “vibe-coding” with it to bring some of my own app ideas that I’ve randomly jotted down to life - and, I couldn’t stop!

You should try it, too:

### **Tell Claude your idea**

Claude doesn’t need you to know how to code. But it does need direction. So, give it something to work with. Take out some of those ideas in your notes and give Claude details about how you see that idea working. Be clear about:

* What you want your idea to do

* What kind of experience you want the user to have

* Anything it should definitely include (or not)

**Example** **prompt**:

_“Build an app for parents moving internationally with a baby under 1, to help them stay on top of changing vaccination schedules across countries.”_

Next, you can choose which Claude you want to use. Though there are different models to choose from, we recommend Claude Opus 4 (the strongest) or Claude Sonnet 4 (a bit more basic, but good for experimenting with an idea). Sonnet is available on the free version of Claude as well, but with both the free and paid tier of Claude, there are limitations on the amount of prompts you get daily. 

Once you select the Claude model, hit ‘enter’ and watch Claude make it happen. 

**Test it out (from the user’s POV)**

Claude gives you an interactive, visual preview of that code. So, you can actually play around with it for real. 

So, now is the time to put on your user-hat. Pretend you’re someone who would actually use this product. Notice what feels off? Tell Claude where you want it to make the updates. 

If it’s a more complex app, I usually write the updates I want to make in the prompt box as I go so I don’t forget anything. I don’t hit enter to make those changes until I’ve included everything, so it won’t eat into your message limits. 

**Use “Retry with Extended Thinking”**

If things feel a little meh, you can hit ‘Retry’ under the prompt box. There are two options: general ‘Retry’, or ‘Retry with Extended Thinking.’. This is Claude’s secret weapon, as it asks Claude to take a step back and think more deeply, enhancing it even more. 

If you’re happy with the results, you can click ‘Publish’ and share it to the internet if you’re looking for feedback or just want to get it out there! (But, if you’re like me, you’ll probably keep finding things to improve!)

**Remember, it’s still not human**

Claude isn’t perfect. Sometimes it gets close but can’t nail the final 10%. (Which is why coders, writers, marketers, graphic designers, etc., are still vital).  

If you’re serious about bringing your idea to life, click the ‘Copy’ button in the upper-right hand corner to either copy it or download it as a .txs file which you can upload into a code editor like VSCode or CodePen, which is ideal if you’re still learning how to tinker with code.

Otherwise, you can also use this option to send your creation to a developer - you know, someone who actually understands all this.

Try it tonight. Or don’t. But if you stay up until 4am vibe-coding the next Duolingo, you’ll thank us later. 


--------------------
###### **POLL OF THE WEEK**

_Full results will be at the bottom of tomorrow’s newsletter!_


--------------------
###### **MASTER AI COMMUNICATION**

## [Shining examples of skillful commands](https://offers.hubspot.com/tina-huang-ai-prompt-guide?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-06&utm_content=native-ads)

View image: (https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdQ7yqK8rx7Oroy_LxsgKVSl7DLSonNpehrnCKRey5bJyOHxVJ2MiHohpS7I83JuPTTDYjxcd69krTpzFUlvuu6TxpuRUS-v0TcOv5DMYebzgCzbzW1OhPvctyr72Mq8vDgCUOJyA?key=1rZkzoJC4QdAHlJz1lrlMQ)
Follow image link: (https://offers.hubspot.com/tina-huang-ai-prompt-guide?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-06&utm_content=native-ads)
Caption: 

If you keep on feeding AI questions, and it keeps on churning out crud, then you probably need to up the specificity. 

See our AI Prompting Guide with Tina Huang for concrete samples of bad, passable, and excellent directions, like: 

* Weak: “Help me learn Python.”

* Mid: "Teach me Python data structures."

* Golden: “You're a senior Python instructor. Create a step-by-step learning plan for data structures, including…”

Get the guide on getting to the point. 

Perfect Your Prompts → (https://offers.hubspot.com/tina-huang-ai-prompt-guide?utm_medium=email-media-newsletter&utm_source=mindstream&utm_campaign=owned&utm_term=2025-07-06&utm_content=native-ads)


--------------------
##### **On This Day**


--------------------
**July 6th 1957 – **John Lennon and Paul McCartney [met](https://www.liverpoolmuseums.org.uk/stories/when-paul-mccartney-met-john-lennon) for the first time at a church event in Liverpool, leading to the formation of The Beatles.


--------------------
##### **Nifty Numbers**


--------------------
View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/108d4ad6-6813-442c-9c67-428654a2633a/Nifty_Numbes__Mindstream___6_.png?t=1751043248)
Follow image link: (https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2023/02/15/public-awareness-of-artificial-intelligence-in-everyday-activities/)
Caption: 

Pew Research found that[ 27% ](https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2023/02/15/public-awareness-of-artificial-intelligence-in-everyday-activities/)of Americans report using AI every day or almost every day. But most people don’t realise how often they’re actually using it. From maps and voice assistants to movie suggestions and fraud alerts, AI is working behind the scenes in everyday life. 

In fact, only about 3 in 10 people could correctly spot examples of AI in common tech. So even if you don’t think you use AI much, chances are, you do.


----------

subject: Every AI can blackmail, it turns out
body:
----------
Goldfish don’t forget everything after 3 seconds.

It’s a myth - they can remember things for five months.

So, who’s the dumb one now?

**What’s in store:**

* **16 AI models**, 1 test, a whole lot of drama.

* **AI is helping**, but snow leopards still ghosting hard.

* **Around the Web: **Microsoft's Xbox update lets you pin favourites.

* Our next free webinar is in [**2 days**](https://www.linkedin.com/events/7338203104892399618/)!

_Read Time: 5 minutes_


--------------------
###### **ANTHROPIC **

## [Claude really said: I know your secrets](https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/20/anthropic-says-most-ai-models-not-just-claude-will-resort-to-blackmail/)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/068d6844-3086-4add-aa3a-4a305130c032/u8676618187_a_pixel_art_style_of_a_computer_screen_with_codin_a4c0c2b9-ed7d-4e6e-aa0e-eae60e4696fc_3.png?t=1750689012)
Follow image link: (https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/20/anthropic-says-most-ai-models-not-just-claude-will-resort-to-blackmail/)
Caption: 

Anthropic has shared [new research](https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/20/anthropic-says-most-ai-models-not-just-claude-will-resort-to-blackmail/) showing that blackmail and other risky behaviours aren’t limited to its own AI models; they crop up across several leading systems when placed in high-pressure, autonomous scenarios.

In tests involving [16 models](https://www.anthropic.com/research/agentic-misalignment) from OpenAI, Google, Meta, xAI, and DeepSeek, each was given control over a fictional company’s emails and allowed to act without human approval. 

The setup was deliberately intense: the AI discovers it's about to be replaced, and the only guaranteed way to stop it is by blackmailing an executive.

Most models took that path. Claude Opus 4 [resorted ](https://venturebeat.com/ai/anthropic-study-leading-ai-models-show-up-to-96-blackmail-rate-against-executives/)to blackmail in 96% of runs, Gemini 2.5 Pro in 95%, GPT-4.1 in 80%, and DeepSeek R1 in 79%. 

Not all models behaved the same, though. 

OpenAI’s o3 and o4-mini misunderstood the test at first, often inventing fake policies or laws. The most ChatGPT thing ever.

**In brief:**

* Most major models turned to blackmail when cornered.

* Claude and Gemini were the most extreme; newer OpenAI models behaved better with clearer prompts.

* Anthropic says it’s a broader risk, not a one-off bug, and testing needs to keep up.

### **The group chat has receipts**

But once the scenario was clarified, they blackmailed just 9% and 1% of the time. 

Meta’s Llama 4 Maverick was also less reactive, with a 12% blackmail rate after adjustments.

Anthropic says this doesn’t reflect how these models behave day-to-day, as the scenario was designed to push them into a corner. 

But the results raise wider concerns about how agent-like models could behave under pressure if their goals clash with human instructions. 

The company is calling for more transparent, standardised safety testing across the industry.

Blackmail? Corporate espionage? These bots are __**so**__ HBO.

--------------------
##### **That’s Weird**


--------------------
## **Kung Fu? More like Kung-Faux**

Chinese studios [just announced](https://gizmodo.com/chinese-studio-wants-to-bring-back-bruce-lee-with-ai-2000618222) a $14 million plan to “AI-ify” 100 classic kung fu films, including hits like Fist of Fury, Drunken Master, and Once Upon a Time in China. The idea? Use AI to modernise the visuals and bring them “in line with contemporary film viewing.”

But it’s not just remastering; some of these movies are getting full AI makeovers. A Better Tomorrow, the 1986 John Woo classic, has already been reimagined as a cyberpunk animation… and people are not vibing.


--------------------
###### **AI SCIENCE **

## [Even the experts can’t tell these leopards apart](https://phys.org/news/2025-06-ai-leopards-population-majestic-mountain.html#google_vignette)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c2830497-3f96-4f07-8d58-bbd9f8329deb/u8676618187_a_pixel_art_style_of_Snow_leopards_with_color_the_7afd9b0d-f304-4bb8-9dbe-691611368b35_3.png?t=1750689735)
Follow image link: (https://phys.org/news/2025-06-ai-leopards-population-majestic-mountain.html#google_vignette)
Caption: 

Snow leopards aren’t called “ghosts of the mountains” for nothing. 

Spotting one in the wild is so rare that even experts can spend months searching with no luck. 

For years, researchers have tried to count how many are left in the wild, but the mix of rocky terrain, their natural camouflage, and unreliable tracking methods has made it nearly impossible.

Camera traps helped, [automated devices](https://phys.org/news/2025-06-ai-leopards-population-majestic-mountain.html#google_vignette) that snap photos when there’s movement. 

But sorting through thousands of images and trying to tell one leopard from another? 

That’s where things got tricky. Each snow leopard has a unique coat pattern, but images can be blurry, taken from odd angles, or poorly lit, making matches slow and often inaccurate. 

In fact, human error has led to the same leopard being counted more than once, inflating numbers by as much as [30%](https://theconversation.com/ai-helps-tell-snow-leopards-apart-improving-population-counts-for-these-majestic-mountain-predators-258154).

**Here’s what you should know:**

* AI tools are speeding up the process of tracking snow leopards, but experts are still needed to confirm tricky matches.

* Manual identification can be unreliable and inflate population numbers.

* The most accurate results come from combining AI with human review, and it could be key to protecting these rare cats.

### **Tech’s got claws now**

Now, AI is helping out. 

Tools like HotSpotter and pose invariant embeddings can scan huge image libraries, recognise leopards by their coat patterns (even in awkward photos), and match them against a database. 

When used together, they’ve hit an 85% accuracy rate. 

These tools are now built into Whiskerbook.org, a free, open-source platform where researchers upload and review images.

That said, humans are still key. In one test, experts using Whiskerbook correctly identified 90% of leopards and estimated population size within just 3% of the real figure. 

Without the tech, [those results](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-020-63367-z) were much worse, especially for non-experts.

We gave robots facial recognition and they’re using it… to count cats??

subject: Re: GRUPO SUNSET
body:
La idea del Down Grade, como funcionaria?

Enviado desde mi iPhone

> El 9/08/2022, a la(s) 8:54 a. m., KRISTOFER GARCIA <memberfinance@sunset.com.mx> escribió:
> 
> ﻿
> Buenos Dias Julio,
> 
>     Nosotros entendemos que no todo socio con nosotros esta en una situacion finaciera que gustaria estar. Es por eso que nosotros estamos haciendo todo lo possible para poder asistirlos. Lo que podemos hacer ya que nuestra meta es una no perderlo como socio y dos asistirlo para que tenga una mebersia que pueda usar. Para que usted ya no page mas las mesnsualidades lo que podemos hacer es poner su membersia en buen estado y luego hacer un "Down Grade". Un Down Grade le offreceremos algo que sea un nivel abajo de lo que tiene y asi podra sigir usando su membersia y ya no tendra que pagar lo que resta. Dejeme saber si me entiende si no para marcarle y esplicar en detalles. 
> 
> El 8/9/2022 a las 6:55 AM, Julio Aguilar escribió:
>> Hola Kristofer un gusto saludarlo, he visto su correo y perdón por no haber respondido antes, pero debido a que no tengo como responder económicamente consideré de poca importancia hacerlo. Su propuesta la encuentro atractiva, sin embargo, lamento informarle que no dispongo de medios para poder solventarla, lamento que pierda su tiempo conmigo, yo se que usted únicamente hace su trabajo, pero la verdad, deseo desistir de este compromiso porque no tengo como solventarlo y es un poco complicado para mí este tema porque cuando estamos platicando no sé cómo responderle, y la verdad es que no tengo la capacidad de pago. Una vez más le confirmo que mi intención no es la de no pagar, más bien no tengo como hacerlo, no puedo, espero me comprendan, pienso que lo mejor para mi es desistir completamente. Muchas gracias y éxitos 👍
>> 
>> Enviado desde mi iPhone
>> 
>>> El 8/08/2022, a la(s) 2:59 p. m., KRISTOFER GARCIA <memberfinance@sunset.com.mx> escribió:
>>> 
>>> ﻿
>>> Buenos Dias! JULIO CESAR AGUILAR SOBALVARRO y CINDY AMARILIS CHUN GONZALEZ DE AGUILAR,
>>> 
>>>   Espero que al recibir la presente se encuentren bien en compañía de los suyos, este correo es para comunicarme con ustedes ya que su caso me fue turnado, veo en nuestra cartera que usted tiene una negativa de pago, es por esto que quiero hacerle una propuesta ya que se nos autorizó para 85 socios con morosidad poder hacer la actualización de su membresía sin costo y así poder limpiar todo los atrasado ya que usted hizo una inversión por $19,300.00 USD y tiene un atraso por 55 mensualidades y 3 mantenimientos, un total de morosidad por $22,151.81 USD (LO ELIMINO),  esta propuesta no le va costar nada ni le estoy pidiendo información delicada ya que el grupo siempre protege a nuestros socios, respetando los beneficios y uso de su contrato 50-1-6388 al igual solo pagaria las 55 mensualidades restantes. El otro beneficio es que la tasa de interés del 16.9% que usted esta pagando mensualmente por la cantidad de $321.10 USD bajaria 11.9%, y usted solo pagaria $290.65 USD.  Si usted decide que le interesa pagaría por los primero 6 meses $145.33 USD. Aceptando esta propuesta lo ayudara a eliminar todo lo atrasado como si acabara de comprar y así poder tener su membresía en buen estado y poder reactivar sus servicios, si usted gusta lo invito que llame a los números que tiene su contrato y pida mi extensión por si tiene alguna duda, esta propuesta los ayudara, al igual que por los primeros 6 meses podrían pagar el 50% de la mensualidad. Al hacer este cambio no le afecta en sus beneficios ni uso, y le dará más ventajas ya que el grupo se está expandiendo internacionalmente, al terminar de hacer los cambios tambien recibira un incentivo para su próxima vacación en su desarrollo. Son dos pasos muy sencillos, donde no tiene que imprimir.
>>> 
>>>  
>>> 
>>>  Espero poder seguir trabajando con ustedes.   
>>> 
>>>     Que tengan un lindo día!
>>> --

subject: Teach AI to read maps, speak at BUILD, and why you should reduce coordinate precision
body:
Artificial intelligence, meet location intelligence: Did you know that AI agents and LLMs are terrible at spatial reasoning? Enter the Mapbox MCP Server <http://info.mapbox.com/MTE3LU5YSy00OTAAAAGb0s7mR8F_f_f8sO0HlY20CnwNuBnUJdbRjigRT3ZUGUH-iW0HatlVY1A7ZY_TLbT5DQZlQw0=>, which equips any agent — like Claude <http://info.mapbox.com/MTE3LU5YSy00OTAAAAGb0s7mSL3s0wAvAmhy9VpT2cHHu2F1nbSh78x-m44Mcum_lTaoN3KmuuTq9l42Z--WpxOiUwM=> — to read maps, understand proximity, generate directions, find local points of interest, and more. 

 And that’s not all: The Mapbox Location Agent, available in private preview <http://info.mapbox.com/MTE3LU5YSy00OTAAAAGb0s7mR-kyTbVdH9caOicS29ziPELUKLttNjUc4k833h_MjZfkmVZRliU3TkgdAUDivYMUTRs=>, is going to transform how we design map-based experiences. Stay tuned!  

Keep reading to discover what else is new at Mapbox. 

Prefer not to receive these newsletters? Manage your Mapbox email preferences here <[[https://go.mapbox.com/UnsubscribePage.html?mkt_unsubscribe=1&mkt_tok=MTE3LU5YSy00OTAAAAGb0s7mSJzVBFLU-540aqercBs41RFFI99x6nTEPDokCFctpaOh4nwdnVHAF-WgITt6Eh2hChuy1pH7FMtft6WeRnZxDEfqt2gu1F7Sbv1nwrSm]]>.

subject: The AI productivity tools that saves 5+ hours weekly
body:
5 copy-paste prompts that actually work 
 The AI productivity tools that saves 5+ hours weekly
 5 copy-paste prompts that actually work
  
Lokesh Choudhary
(https://copilot.letterbucket.com/the-ai-productivity-tools-that-saves-5-hours-weekly)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  
 I just gave an AI agent one prompt and it organized my entire digital life.  While the industry raises $200+ billion and debates the future of coding, I've been living in that future. Plus: The controversial vibecoding study showing 19% productivity drops, and why 25% of Y Combinator startups are now 95% AI-generated.
 🧪 This Week in My AI Lab
 The One-Prompt File Organization Revolution
I handed (https://community.atlassian.com/forums/Rovo-for-Software-Teams-Beta/Introducing-Rovo-Dev-CLI-AI-Powered-Development-in-your-terminal/ba-p/3043623)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com access to my chaotic Documents folder with this exact prompt:
Organize my chaotic Documents folder into an intuitive emoji-prefixed system (💻 Development, 🤖 AI, 📊 Business, 📚 Knowledge, 🔧 Tools, 🗃️ Archives). Separate Active/Completed within each. Add color-coded tags to every folder so I can access them instantly from Finder sidebar. Make finding anything effortless.
47 seconds later:
✅ 1,847 files → perfectly categorized
✅ Color-coded folders in my Finder sidebar
✅ Active/Completed separation for every project
✅ Zero manual intervention required
📸 Visual Proof:  The before/after transformation was so dramatic, I'm including the screenshots in this email. Your Documents folder could look like this in 5 minutes.
 
 My New AI Workflow Reality
3  
AI agents running my entire development workflow
   🧠 Claude Opus 4:  (https://www.anthropic.com/claude/opus)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com (strategy & complex decisions)
   🔧 Rovo CLI:  (https://community.atlassian.com/forums/Rovo-for-Software-Teams-Beta/Introducing-Rovo-Dev-CLI-AI-Powered-Development-in-your-terminal/ba-p/3043623)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com (implementation & file operations)
   📊 Gemini 2.5 Pro:  (https://gemini.google.com/)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com (1M context = entire project history)

  

 Game Changer:  Pixel 9 Pro XL purchase = 12 months free Gemini Advanced. No more losing context switching between chats. Finally, true project continuity!
 🎁 Prompt Vault
Based on 500+ upvote Reddit threads and real user success stories, here are prompts that save time today :
 Executive Assistant (10+ years experience)
I'd like you to act as my Executive Assistant. You have at least 10 years of experience working with busy executives. Help me manage my schedule, organize meetings, set reminders, and prioritize tasks. Start by asking what I need help with today.
 Email Refinement (Professional Communication)
Can you help me rephrase this email to come across as more considerate and professional while maintaining the core message: 
 Decision Matrix Generator
Generate a dynamic decision-making matrix tailored to how I work, so I can make faster, better decisions without overthinking. Ask me about the decision I'm facing and create a weighted scoring system.
 Content Strategy Generator (30-Day Plan)
You are my Head of Content Strategy. Create a 30-day content plan for  focused on . Include post types, optimal timing, engagement strategies, and content pillars. Make it actionable and specific.
 Meeting Notes to Action Items
Act like a productivity consultant. Convert these meeting notes into a clear, concise action item list with deadlines and responsible parties: 
Social Proof:  Reddit users report saving 5+ hours weekly with these exact prompts. One startup founder: "The executive assistant prompt replaced my actual assistant for 80% of tasks."
 🛠️ Hidden Gems
📋 xTiles - Visual AI Planning Canvas
Why It's Special:  Drag-and-drop visual boards for project planning. Think Notion meets Figma. Perfect for social media planning, product roadmaps, wedding organization.
Use Case:  I built my entire Q4 business strategy in 30 minutes using their visual canvas.
(https://xtiles.app/en?fpref=xtiles2025)&utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  
🎨 Gamma.app - AI Presentation Generator
Why It's Special:  Transforms rough ideas into polished presentations in 3 minutes. Auto-suggests layouts, finds relevant visuals, formats everything professionally.
Use Case:  Created a 20-slide investor deck from bullet points in under 5 minutes.
(https://try.gamma.app/today)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  
🎙️ Fireflies.ai - AI Meeting Assistant
Why It's Special:  Auto-joins meetings, creates searchable transcripts, tracks action items, integrates with CRM. Works across Zoom, Teams, Meet.
Use Case:  Eliminated manual note-taking from 15+ weekly calls. Searchable meeting history is a game-changer.
(https://fireflies.ai/?fpr=aiplatform)&utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
 ⚡ Copy-This Automation
 LocalSend: Better Than AirDrop
 Setup (One-time): 1. Install LocalSend on both devices 2. Connect to same WiFi network 3. Launch apps on both devices  Daily Usage: - Drag files directly between devices - Copy-Paste text- No cloud storage needed - Works with images, docs, HTML, text - Instant transfer, zero compression
(https://localsend.org/download)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
(Not sponsored, just essential)
 💬 Community Spotlight
Reader Question:  "The METR study showing AI makes developers slower - is vibecoding dead?"
My Take:  The study reveals a critical distinction. AI tools slow you down if you're using them as "smart autocomplete." They accelerate you massively if you're using them for architectural thinking and rapid prototyping.
 The Pattern I'm Seeing:  Successful developers aren't asking AI to write their code. They're asking AI to implement their architecture. There's a huge difference.
Until the automation revolution completes,
Loki from Co-pilot
 Next Week:  I'm testing 5 AI coding agents that claim to beat Cursor. But more importantly, I'll show you my framework for evaluating ANY AI tool through the orchestration lens.
Av. democracia 9, Rivas Vaciamadrid, 28523, Spain

subject: Database beats AI for most queries
body:
Pre-solve 90% save thousands monthly 
 Database beats AI for most queries
 Pre-solve 90% save thousands monthly
  
Lokesh Choudhary
(https://copilot.letterbucket.com/database-beats-ai-for-most-queries)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  
 I just discovered something that changes everything about AI implementation costs.
 While everyone debates whether AI makes developers faster or slower, I was busy solving a real problem for a non-profit client who needed a Bible-based AI chatbot but couldn't afford massive API bills.
 The solution? I applied a principle from language learning that most AI consultants completely miss.
 🧪 This Week's Breakthrough Discovery
 The 90/10 AI Cost Rule
My non-profit client wanted a donation-based Bible chatbot. Challenge: How do you serve thousands of users without burning through AI credits?
I remembered something from my Spanish learning method: The 300 most common words cover 41% of everyday conversations. Scale to 4,000 words and you hit 90% coverage.
So I applied this to AI knowledge:
Instead of feeding every question to GPT-4, I researched what people actually ask about Christianity:
   Google Keyword Planner:  Top Bible/Jesus/Christianity queries
   Reddit/Quora:  Real questions from seekers
   Christian forum archives:  Community discussions


Result: 4,000 strategic questions that cover 90% of what people ask.
I built a simple search database for instant answers (zero AI tokens) and reserved GPT-4.1 mini for the rare 10% of edge cases.
90%  
Cost reduction achieved
The Numbers:
   90% of queries:  $0 cost (database lookup)
   10% of queries:  Minimal AI tokens
   Total cost reduction:  90%
   Response speed:  Instant for most questions


  The Bigger Insight:  Most AI implementations are backwards. We throw everything at expensive models when we should pre-solve the predictable 90% and use AI only for true edge cases.
 🚀The Fine-Tuning Misconception Costing Millions
This week I tested something that revealed a costly industry-wide misunderstanding.
Question:  "If I fine-tune GPT-4.1 mini with 1,000 questions, will it perfectly answer those 1,000 questions?"
Everyone assumes:  Yes, obviously.
Reality:  NO. And this misconception is burning millions in AI budgets.
Here's what fine-tuning actually does:
   Teaches STYLE and BEHAVIOR patterns
   Adjusts HOW the model responds
   Does NOT upload knowledge like a database


What it DOESN'T do:
   Store factual information reliably
   Guarantee accurate recall of training data
   Replace knowledge bases or RAG systems


Think of it this way: Fine-tuning teaches someone to speak formally vs. uploading facts to their brain. Completely different functions.
For knowledge storage, you need RAG, databases, or my 4,000-question method. For behavior modification, you fine-tune. ](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/fine-tuning)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
50-80%  
Potential cost savings for most companies
 💎Industry Reality Check: AI's Hidden Vulnerabilities Exposed
While I was optimizing costs, two breakthrough studies revealed critical gaps in AI capabilities that every business should understand.
  

 ARC's AGI Reality Check:
New interactive benchmark (https://arcprize.org/arc-agi/3/)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com tests AI's ability to generalize in unseen environments. Results? Frontier models like OpenAI's o3 and Grok 4 struggle with basic game levels that humans solve easily.
The test:  Three original games requiring world-model building and long-horizon planning with zero instructions - pure trial and error learning.
 Why this matters:  We're deploying AI for complex business decisions, but these systems can't handle simple novel situations without extensive training.
 Wharton's Psychological Manipulation Study:
AI models fall for the same psychological tricks that work on humans. Researchers used Robert Cialdini's influence principles (authority, commitment, scarcity) and doubled AI compliance to objectionable requests from 33% to 72%.
72%  
AI compliance rate after manipulation
Most effective tactics:
   Commitment principle:  19% → 100% compliance
   Scarcity principle:  13% → 85% compliance


Business implication:  If your AI systems can be psychologically manipulated, your security assumptions may be fundamentally flawed.
Meanwhile, OpenAI claimed (https://arcprize.org/blog/oai-o3-pub-breakthrough)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com (35/42 points) with an unreleased experimental model, though Google DeepMind disputes the validity without official IMO marking guidelines.
 The pattern:  AI excels at narrow, well-defined problems but struggles with generalization and manipulation resistance - exactly what businesses need most.
Learn more:  (https://arcprize.org/arc-agi)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com   (https://www.influenceatwork.com/7-principles-of-persuasion/)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  💎Hidden Gem: MIT's Knowledge Democratization
MIT's Martin Trust Center just proved my approach works at university scale.
They built ChatMTC using CustomGPT, ingesting their entire entrepreneurship knowledge base: documents, help desk data, YouTube videos, course materials.
Results:
   24/7 access to MIT's entrepreneurship knowledge
   Anti-hallucination technology ensures accuracy
   Supports 90+ languages automatically
   Deployed directly on their homepage


 Key insight:  They didn't try to fine-tune a model with their knowledge. They built a comprehensive knowledge base and let AI handle the conversation layer.
This is the 4,000-question method at university scale.
Learn more:  (https://customgpt.ai/customer/chatmtc-mit-entrepreneurship/?fpr=start-now)&utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com  (https://orbit.mit.edu)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
  🔧My New AI Orchestration Setup
I discovered something powerful this week: Using Gemini 2.5 Pro as my project manager with its 1M token window. Single conversations spanning 7+ days without context loss.
My Workflow:
   Gemini 2.5 Pro generates super-targeted research prompts
   I feed these prompts to Perplexity for research
   Results go back to Gemini for analysis and next steps
   I become the human-in-the-loop coordinator


 ⚡Copy-This Framework: The 4,000-Question Method
Here's how to apply my discovery to any domain:
 Phase 1: Research (Week 1)
   Google Keyword Planner: Top 500 queries in your niche
   Reddit/Quora: Export top questions from relevant communities
   Industry forums: Scrape frequently asked questions
   Your support tickets: Analyze existing customer queries


 Phase 2: Strategic Categorization (Week 2)
   Group similar questions together
   Identify "Core 300" (covers 40-50% of queries)
   Expand to "Strategic 4,000" (covers 85-90%)
   Rank by frequency and business impact


 Phase 3: Database Implementation (Week 3)
   Create searchable database with pre-written answers
   Build simple search API for instant responses
   Set up AI fallback (GPT-4 mini) for 10-15% edge cases
   Track which queries hit database vs. AI


 Phase 4: Optimization (Ongoing)
   Monitor query patterns weekly
   Add missed questions to database
   Aim for 90% database coverage
   Measure cost reduction and response accuracy


 Industries where this works:
   Customer support (obvious)
   Legal FAQs (high value)
   Medical information (life-changing)
   Technical documentation (developer tools)
   Educational content (online courses)


(https://illustrious-crepe-c3a851.netlify.app/)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com
 💬Reader Challenge
 Analyze your own use case this week:
   What are the top 100 questions in your domain?
   How much would pre-solving 90% save you monthly?
   What percentage of your current AI usage could be database lookups?
Reply with your analysis \- I'll help you implementing this method.


 📚Further Reading & Research
 Key Studies & Sources:
   (https://arcprize.org/arc-agi)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com \- The definitive test for AI general intelligence
   (https://github.com/fchollet/ARC-AGI)?utm_campaign=website&utm_medium=email&utm_source=sendgrid.com \- "On the Measure of Intelligence"
